The paper deals with analyzing inconsistency in pairwise comparisons, which is a topic in decision making and optimization. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The use of abelian groups and linearly ordered groups also suggests a connection to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical and theoretical reasons for normalizing inconsistency indicators, which could be relevant to the fields of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
